    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Executive Parachutes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gregoire Landel letter wonders why executives continue to receive enormous payoffs for poor performance (June 16 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Another Coke Classic'' (editorial, June 16): Perhaps we should also question the practice of giving enormous payoffs to any executive departing for poor performance. Most employees who get fired for being unqualified or inadequate are not given golden parachutes, so why should executives?</p>
        <p>GRÉGOIRE LANDEL  New York, June 16, 2004</p>
      </block>
